BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:j05-programme-2026@usa-roadtrip
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:🥾 J05 - Yosemite Valley (Mist Trail) → Bass Lake
DESCRIPTION:06h30 Départ Sweetwater → Yosemite Valley (Tunnel View en chemin)\n07h30 Parking Upper Pines\n07h45 Navette → Happy Isles\n07h45-12h00 Mist Trail : Vernal Fall + Nevada Fall (12\,8 km\, 815m D+\, ~5h30)\n12h45 Navette → El Capitan Meadow\n13h00-14h00 El Capitan (vue paroi 900m\, grimpeurs)\n14h15-15h30 Yosemite Falls (Lower Yosemite Fall Trail 1\,6 km)\n16h00 Route Yosemite → Bass Lake (~80-100 km\, 1h30-2h)\n18h30 Check-in Oh Ridge Campground - site 141 (Deer)\n🏕️ Oh Ridge Campground - Bass Lake - conf. reservation-camping-12-07.pdf
CATEGORIES:Programme
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:j06-programme-2026@usa-roadtrip
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260713
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260714
SUMMARY:🏜️ J06 - Oh Ridge → Father Crowley → Death Valley
DESCRIPTION:07h00 Petit-déjeuner + check-out Oh Ridge\n08h00-08h30 Plein d'essence (Bishop ou zone June Lake)\n08h30-11h30 Route Oh Ridge → Father Crowley (~200 km\, US-395 S + CA-190 E)\n11h30-12h30 Father Crowley Vista Point (canyon spectaculaire\, marche bord du canyon)\n12h30-13h00 Pique-nique sur place\n13h00-14h30 Route → Death Valley (traversée Panamint Valley\, CA-190)\n14h30-16h00 Mesquite Flat Sand Dunes (Stovepipe Wells)\n16h00-17h00 Route → Furnace Creek\n17h00 Check-in The Ranch at Death Valley\n18h00 Piscine (source chaude incluse)\, dîner\n⚠️ Chaleur : 28-45°C - beaucoup d'eau indispensable\n🏕️ The Ranch at Death Valley (Furnace Creek) - conf. reservation-camping-13-07.pdf
